Simone Schloss

EdLab Staff

Simone believes in the power of communication.

For more than a decade, I performed cabaret, choral, and a cappella music. About two years into the cabarets, I first experienced performance anxiety. My right leg shook uncontrollably from the knee down. It was as if it wasnt part of me. I firmly anchored my foot and soldiered on. To my surprise, no one was the wiser, but I wondered how I would manage, going forward.

The experience unnerved me. I considered keeping it to myself. Instead, I talked to my peers. At the next show, months later, I steeled myself. Nothing happened. In fact, I never again experienced performance anxiety. I credit that to not having kept my problem a secret.

Simone believes in the power of reinvention.

Simone Schloss graduated from Simmons College in 2017 with an MLIS, and honors from Beta Phi Mu, the International Library & Information Studies Honor Society. She served as Treasurer of the SLA (Special Library Association), Simmons student chapter. Simone concentrated in business topics such as: Knowledge Management; Competitive Intelligence; Business Reference; Data and Records Management; and Corporate Librarianship. She built a website about her vocal performance career, using Dreamweaver: http://www.specialform.org/users/slsweb/.

During her Fall 2016 internship at the Lilly Music Library, Tufts University, Simone: digitized recordings, using Audacity; evaluated sheet music donations; and helped develop the cabaret collection. Simone curated a cabaret exhibit that includes the story of musical theater star Barbara Cookes reinvention as a solo concert artist.  See photos, below. Check out Simones rhizr for tips on the weekly commute between New York and Boston: http://rhizr.com/rz/CnvfYhpX7gg6JzuLj/from-new-york-to-boston.

Simone believes in the power of experience.

Previously, Simone graduated from the Wharton School, University of Pennsylvania, with an MBA. For nearly a decade, she was an analyst at: the NYC Mayors OMB (Office of Management and Budget); General Motors TONY (Treasurers Office, NY); and the Federal Reserve Board (Washington, DC.) Simone graduated magna cum laude from Princeton University with a bachelor's degree in Economics. She is proficient in French, and was awarded a certificate from the Sorbonne University during her junior summer semester abroad.

Follow Simone Schloss on LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/in/simoneschloss/ and Twitter https://twitter.com/simoneschloss.
